premise_source_doc_sentence: David Michael `` Dave '' Navarro  (  born June 7 , 1967  )  is an American guitarist , singer , songwriter , and actor .
Navarro is best known as a founding member of the alternative rock band Jane 's Addiction  (  four studio albums  )  and as a former member of the Red Hot Chili Peppers  (  one album  )  .
He also released one solo album Trust No One  (  2001  )  .
Navarro has also been a member of the Jane 's Addiction spin-off bands , Deconstruction and The Panic Channel .
Allmusic 's Greg Prato described him as `` one of alternative rock 's first true guitar heroes '' , with an eclectic playing style that merges heavy metal , psychedelia , and modern rock .
Outside of music , Navarro is known as the host and one of the judges on Ink Master , an American tattoo competition reality show now in its eighth season on Spike .
A drummer and percussionist , he currently plays with Jane 's Addiction and Hellflower .
The band originally had wanted Dave Navarro as their guitarist but Navarro 's band , Jane 's Addiction had just broken up and he was n't ready to join another band .
Dave Navarro went on to join the Red Hot Chili Peppers later that year and participate in Jane 's Addiction reunions in 1997 and 2001 .
Deconstruction was a band formed by former Jane 's Addiction members , guitarist Dave Navarro and bassist Eric Avery .

In 1992 , he appeared as percussionist on Rage Against the Machine 's `` Know Your Enemy '' and in 1995 , contributed percussion to the Red Hot Chili Peppers songs `` One Big Mob '' and `` Warped '' on their album One Hot Minute  (  fellow Jane 's Addiction member Dave Navarro was the guitarist for the Chili Peppers during the making of that album  )  .
